The paper deals with outlier detection, which is a common problem in data management and machine learning. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is a likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel mixed integer programming formulation for selecting and executing outlier detectors, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also incorporates meta-learning for evaluating the cost and utility of detectors, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the visualization of outlier detection results, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of outlier detection in security applications, which is related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
